In order to run this you need the following steps:

1. figure out your local IP address. In my case, when I run:
  lstoppa@C02DL3AAMD6R splunk-connect-for-snmp % ifconfig| grep "inet "
        inet 127.0.0.1 netmask 0xff000000
        inet 192.168.1.114 netmask 0xffffff00 broadcast 192.168.1.255
        inet 10.127.60.203 netmask 0xffffffff broadcast 10.127.60.203

  in my case, 10.127.60.203 is reachable from docker, so that's the one I need to use.
  In your case, the IP address will be different.
2. figure out your HEC tocken
3. verify that the index name specified in otel-doc-example-old.yaml exists in your local Splunk.
   In my case I was using the one used for the poller testing "snmp"
4. open a terminal, navigate to the folder "otel", and run
   lstoppa@C02DL3AAMD6R otel % docker-compose up
    WARNING: Found orphan containers (otel_otel-opentelemetry-collector-contrib_1, otel_opentelemetry-collector-contrib_1, otel_otel-collector-contrib_1) for this project. If you removed or renamed this service in your compose file, you can run this command with the --remove-orphans flag to clean it up.
