5. Open a new terminal, and run the following command (no need to change anything, port 9999 is the correct one
   for everyone)
    lstoppa@C02DL3AAMD6R splunk-connect-for-snmp % curl http://localhost:9999 -d '{"event": "I am an HEC event from OTEL", "sourcetype": "metric"}'
6. Check in Splunk Web that the new event is there:
    18/03/2021 14:20:11.000
    I am an HEC event from OTEL
    host = unknownsource = otelsourcetype = metric